			<ns0:name>mcgra...@chromium.org</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/109286297231979736865/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">This is a tracking bug for the unresolved questions about file-opening calls of various sorts and their implications for the integrated runtime plan.

All the details of IPC-based solutions for file access of different kinds should be hidden in the IRT.  In the ABI exposed by the IRT we need to define one or more &amp;quot;open&amp;quot;-like calls for different purposes, and all other calls relating to file names (stat, getdents) that might be needed.

It's an open issue with multiple moving parts how to address this.
Be sure to get it squared away in the irt.h ABI definition once it starts to gel.
